name: Medusae - Marivagia Stellata
description: What can jellyfish teach us about climate change? Warming of temperatures, oxygen depletion and ocean acidification, coupled with overfishing and invasive species, are giving jellyfish advantage over other marine life. Marivagia Stellata, first spotted in 2006 off the coast of Israel, has star-burst like pattern on the round body. Half of the profit made with this series Medusae will be donated to WWF Mediterranean to help protect the Mediterranean Sea.
